Architecture decision (user-directed, this session): memory store cutover to human-readable md files. Canonical: .gm/memories/<key>.md for project facts, .gm/disciplines/<name>/memories/<key>.md for transferable discipline knowledge (auto-create unknown disciplines at memorize time, never mix into project store). Frontmatter key/ns/created/updated; UTF-8 no BOM, LF. Vector/embedding index = derived transient state rebuilt on content-digest mismatch (sync-before-emit), never tracked. rs-learn crate retires: its live surface was only LearnSession/dispatch_json + KvBackend (recall/memorize/prune) -- embedding already in rs-plugkit (rs-learn embeddings.rs is one EMBED_DIM const), router/adapter/fisher loop a witnessed no-op, rs-learn.db 50 tables ~all empty (23 episodes only). rs-search stays as the ranking rlib over both corpora. 784-memory corpus exported to .gm/memories/ with idempotent exporter (f.f=f witnessed under real crash-loop re-runs). Broken libsql vector DELETE stops being load-bearing: prune = file delete + mark-deleted flag. Legacy flat-JSON KV stays the live read path until rs-plugkit md cutover lands (durability rule: never regress mid-cutover).